Q.Pwds.RW.React: I do not need to replace any of the passwords reported as weak or reused.
Q.Pwds.RW.React.N_3_TEXT: The sites with weak passwords have a limit on the length or characteristics of the password, so it is impossible to have a stronger password for these sites. The sites reported as weak are actually a duplicate of the same site.
Q.Pwds.C.React: I do not need to replace any of the passwords reported as compromised.
Q.Pwds.C.React.N_3_TEXT: The sites with supposedly compromised passwords have very short limits on the length of the passwords, such as 4-digit numerical pincodes. All 10,000 4-digit numbers would appear on the list of compromised passwords, so changing the PIN for these sites to another 4-digit number would still leave it with a code on the list of compromised passwords. If the sites would let me use a longer password, I would.
